<TITLE>Itzhak Bentov</TITLE>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name" NEW="yes">Itzhak Bentov</REFEX>
</REF>
 (1923 - May 25, 1979) was a Czech born scientist, inventor, mystic and author. 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="2" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 was an early exponent of what has come to be referred to as consciousness studies.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="3" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name_family" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name_family" NEW="yes">Bentov</REFEX>
</REF>
 was born in Czechoslovakia and 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="4" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="no_case_empty" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="empty" CASE="no_case" TAG="no_case_empty" NEW="yes">_</REFEX>
</REF>
 moved to Israel. In Israel, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="5" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 was part of the fledgling state's scientific unit, the Hemmed, where 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="6" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 designed Israel's first rocket for the War of Independence. The Hemmed had to make improvised weapons as there was a world-wide embargo on selling weapons to the Jewish state.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
After the war, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="7" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 moved to America where 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="8" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 followed 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="9" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj-det" PREDICTION="genitive_pronoun_his" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="genitive" TAG="genitive_pronoun_his" NEW="yes">his</REFEX>
</REF>
 passion as an inventor. 
By profession 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="10" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 was a mechanical engineer specialising in Biomedical Engineering and instrumentation. 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="11" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 is credited with the invention of the remote controlled cardiac catheter (US Patent Sep., 1971 Bentov. )
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="12" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name_family" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name_family" NEW="yes">Bentov</REFEX>
</REF>
 was also an accomplished meditator.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
By blending analytical knowledge and intuitive insight, 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="13" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 was the first to develop what is now widely accepted as a holographic model of reality.
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="14" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj-det" PREDICTION="genitive_pronoun_his" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="genitive" TAG="genitive_pronoun_his" NEW="yes">his</REFEX>
</REF>
 best known work is Stalking the Wild Pendulum: On the Mechanics of Consciousness (1977) in which 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="15" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="nominative_pronoun_he" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="nominative" TAG="nominative_pronoun_he" NEW="yes">he</REFEX>
</REF>
 described 
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="16" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj-det" PREDICTION="genitive_pronoun_his" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="pronoun" CASE="genitive" TAG="genitive_pronoun_his" NEW="yes">his</REFEX>
</REF>
 theory of The Continuous Big Bang Universe a form of Eternal return. (Its title was a play on that of 
<REF ENTITY="1" MENTION="1" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj-det" PREDICTION="genitive_name" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="1" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="genitive" TAG="genitive_name" NEW="yes">Euell Gibbons'</REFEX>
</REF>
 popular 1962 book Stalking the Wild Asparagus.)
</PARAGRAPH>

<PARAGRAPH>
<REF ENTITY="0" MENTION="17" SEMCAT="person" SYNCAT="np" SYNFUNC="subj" PREDICTION="plain_name_family" CHOICE="1">
<REFEX ENTITY="0" REG08-TYPE="name" CASE="plain" TAG="plain_name_family" NEW="yes">Bentov</REFEX>
</REF>
 died in the American Airlines Flight 191 disaster at O'Hare International Airport in Chicago on May 25, 1979.
</PARAGRAPH>
